## Limitations

The findings presented are based on available data and surveys, which may not fully capture the diversity of opinions across different demographics and regions. Additionally, public opinion is subject to change over time, influenced by new scientific findings, political developments, and media coverage. The reliance on surveys also means that the data is self-reported, which can introduce biases or inaccuracies in how individuals perceive and report their views on climate change.